I just so happened to be in the area post finishing a spin class workout at CycleBar for a Yelp event. Catching CTA Morgan at the time enroute to and leaving the spin class I took a look on Morgan St to see what businesses were near and lo and behold, Shake Shack was off to the side. I have actually been procrastinating on visiting the location in Skokie for sometime now since discovering it, thanks to Yelper - Passhon J. Since I have visited this location I can now cease that visit because I was not fond of locating Shake Shack inside of the Old Orchard Shopping Center at all. Now, despite this location not being inside of a shopping center like the Skokie one, its interior appeared the same. And I loved that its menu was plastered up on the wall, and readable!  As for its menu, out of a list that consisted of burgers, chicken, hot dogs, and fries, plus several drinks, beer & wine, I ordered the Chick'n Shack which is a crispy chicken breast sandwich with lettuce, pickles and buttermilk herbo mayo. In the future I would love to return and try one of their burgers because it's what built that interest to visit Shake Shack in the first place. And I did love that they give a restaurant pager letting you know that your order is ready at the counter.  As for the Chick'n Shack, it was fresh, hot, and tasty! And damn well worth trying if you are contemplating something to try on their menu or if you love chicken sandwiches.  During this visit, the employees were courteous and friendly! Once I finished my meal I was buried in my phone Yelping, and one of the employees took my tray despite me sitting right next to the trash receptacle. I was also startled by one who greeted me, asking how am I doing once I finish my meal which I rarely get anywhere unless its once I walk through the door. Big plus, Shake Shack!  In closing, Shake Shack surpassed my expectations and since I now know what to expect at this location I would not hesitate on visiting again. And besides, it just gives me an excuse to visit Fulton Market District again.  ~Blessings all~  Thomas G

We happened to be nearby and in need of lunch. This place has good reviews, so we walked on over.  It's a cute little place - I love their seating in particular. The employees were wearing these great t-shirts referencing Pride month, which was nice to see. Being in a bit of a hurry, we all ordered burgers. They were hot and juicy and flavorful - really yummy - and the fries were good. Maybe not spectacular, but quite good.  Their prices are a bit high for being what is essentially a fancier diner; $5 for just a burger then $2.99 for fries is perhaps a bit much but not unusual. However, the $5.50 for a root beer float that consists literally of a cup of root beer with a single small scoop of ice cream is bloody well ridiculous! I expect the food prices to be a bit higher in the city, since the costs are higher, but the price for that float just killed me. Particularly as I'd gone there for that. Given that their name is "shake shack", I figured their ice cream things would be particularly good. The shakes might be really good but that float wasn't worth the price, let alone writing home about...
